{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:job.7",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 7,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 7",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 7 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:job.7.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:1",
      "text": "The life of man upon earth is a warfare, and his days are like the days of a hireling.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.7.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:2",
      "text": "As a servant longeth for the shade, as the hireling looketh for the end of his work;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.7.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:3",
      "text": "So I also have had empty months, and have numbered to myself wearisome nights.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.7.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:4",
      "text": "If I lie down to sleep, I shall say: When shall I rise? and again, I shall look for the evening, and shall be filled with sorrows even till darkness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.7.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:5",
      "text": "My flesh is clothed with rottenness and the filth of dust; my skin is withered and drawn together.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.7.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:6",
      "text": "My days have passed more swiftly than the web is cut by the weaver, and are consumed without any hope.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.7.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:7",
      "text": "Remember that my life is but wind, and my eye shall not return to see good things.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.7.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:8",
      "text": "Nor shall the sight of man behold me: thy eyes are upon me, and I shall be no more.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.7.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:9",
      "text": "As a cloud is consumed, and passeth away: so he that shall go down to hell shall not come up.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.7.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:10",
      "text": "Nor shall he return any more into his house, neither shall his place know him any more",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.7.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:11",
      "text": "Wherefore, I will not spare my mouth, I will speak in the affliction of my spirit: I will talk with the bitterness of my soul.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.7.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:12",
      "text": "Am I a sea, or a whale, that thou hast enclosed me in a prison?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.7.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:13",
      "text": "If I say: My bed shall comfort me, and I shall be relieved, speaking with myself on my couch:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.7.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:14",
      "text": "Thou wilt frighten me with dreams, and terrify me with visions.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.7.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:15",
      "text": "So that my soul rather chooseth hanging, and my bones death.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.7.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:16",
      "text": "I have done with hope, I shall now live no longer: spare me, for my days are nothing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.7.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:17",
      "text": "What is a man, that thou shouldst magnify him or why dost thou set thy heart upon him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.7.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:18",
      "text": "Thou visitest him early in the morning, and thou provest him suddenly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.7.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:19",
      "text": "How long wilt thou not spare me, nor suffer me to swallow down my spittle?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.7.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:20",
      "text": "I have sinned: what shall I do to thee, O keeper of men? why hast thou set me opposite to thee. and am I become burdensome to myself?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.7.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:21",
      "text": "Why dost thou not remove my sin, and why dost thou not take away my iniquity? Behold now I shall sleep in the dust: and if thou seek me in the morning, I shall not be.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
